    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-11-13T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-11-13T11:00:00-05:00" n="368"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d368">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">815.00/2748: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morales</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-11-13T10:00:00-06:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 13, 1923—10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>93. The Guatemalan Minister acting as the representative of Arias made a
                    proposition to Carias for an arrangement between the two on the basis that Arias
                    be the President. Carias refused to entertain the proposal.</p>
                <pb facs="0569" n="445" xml:id="pg_445"/>
                <p>The President requested my opinion yesterday relative to the advisability of
                    holding a conference with the three candidates for the purpose of trying to
                    effect a satisfactory solution of the question agreeable to all. I heartily
                    approved of the plan.</p>
                <p>There is no immediate danger of a revolution from either Carias or Arias and I
                    believe that if no arrangement can be effected among the candidates that they
                    will await the decision of Congress before resorting to arms.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Guatemala.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Morales</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
